('Fit: snug is not the same as tight','A useful product page should explain size range, stretch, and how the adjustable closure works. “One size fits most” is not enough by itself. Look for measurements in inches or millimeters, photos that show the closure, and instructions that explain how to loosen or remove the ring.\n\nThe practical rule is simple: the product should feel secure enough to stay in place, but not painful, cold, numb, or difficult to remove. Avoid prolonged wear, follow the manufacturer’s time limits, and stop immediately with discomfort. Adults with circulation concerns, nerve issues, recent surgery, or medical questions should ask a qualified clinician rather than relying on a product description.'),
